Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
10 Rose Street, Campbelltown represents a unique opportunity to secure a key land holding in Sydney’s South West Growth Corridor. The land is level and underdeveloped.  The site also boasts a large frontage to Watsford Road (approx. 80m) and has access to Rose Street. The existing building is specialised and has previously been used as cold store facility for milk distribution. 

-	Drive around capabilities
-	All weather awning 
-	Zoned B5 - Business Development
-	4km* to the Hume Highway
-	Proximity to Campbelltown’s Train Station and CBD (600m*).
-	Ongoing surrounding residential re-zoning & development
-	Redevelopment opportunities (STCA)
-       Fit for industrial strata units/storage (STCA)

For further information, to arrange an inspection or to obtain a copy of the information memorandum please contact the exclusive selling agents.

CBRE is pleased to offer Stage 6 of 'Macarthur Heights' estate at Campbelltown, in south western Sydney.

The site is located opposite the Western Sydney University Campbelltown Campus and nearby to Macarthur Train Station, Macarthur Square Shopping Centre and TAFE NSW.

The site can be developed with a range of residential dwellings, including freestanding homes, small lot housing, terraces and residential apartments.

Key features:
- Located within the well regarded 'Macarthur Height's residential estate;
- 900 metres* to Macarthur Train Station;
- Site Area of 7.63 hectares*;
- 950 metres* to the entry of Macarthur Square Shopping Centre;
- Located opposite the Western Sydney University Campus and TAFE NSW;
- Elevated position with district views;
- Project has the ability to be developed in stages; and
- Services are available for connection.

*approx.
